Crockpot Bolognese

4 oz pancetta (or center cut bacon) chopped
1 tbsp butter (or olive oil)
1 large white onion, minced
2 celery stalks (3/4 c) minced
2 medium carrots (3/4 c) minced
2 lb 95% lean ground beef
1/4 c white wine
2x28oz cans crushed tomatoes
3 bay leaves
salt and freshly ground pepper
1/4 c chopped fresh parsley
1/2 c half & half

In a large deep saute pan, saute pancetta on low heat until the fat melts, 4-5 min. Add butter, onions, celery, and carrots, and cook on medium low heat until soft, ~ 5min. Increase to medium high, add meat, season with salt and pepper and saute until browned. Drain the fat then add wine; cook until it reduces down, 3-4 min. Add to crockpot with the tomatoes and bay leaves; season with salt and pepper. Cover and set to low for 6 hrs. Adjust the salt and pepper to taste, add half & half and parsley. Stir and serve over pasta.


Nutrition:
serving size: 1/2 c
calories: 143
Total fat: 7g
Saturated Fat: 3g
Monounsaturated fat: 3g
Cholesterol: 48mg
Sodium: 145 mg
Carbohydrate: 5g
Dietary fiber: 1g
Sugar: 3g
Protein: 15g
Potassium: 452mg
Iron: 10%
Vitamin A: 30%
Vitamin C: 20%
Calcium: 2%
